  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Restoration of Iraq&apos;s Historic and Cultural Heritage as a Pillar for Economic Recovery</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As Iraq is shifting from an emergency to a post-crisis context and lack of job opportunities is widely recognized as a critical need, this project contributes to the recovery of the country by supporting small and medium enterprises with social and cultural value with access to special grants for long-term job creation. Adopting a comprehensive strategy and tailored Enterprise Development Fund culture grants, IOM in partnership with UNESCO is developing specific selection criteria to determine and provide assistance to enterprises that directly contribute to the restoration of cultural heritage, have the capacity to create or support jobs, and are scalable in the long-term. The intervention aims to target internally displaced persons, returnees and host community in the area of Ninewa and Basra governorates, with a particular focus on the old cities of Mosul and Basra.</narrative>
  </description>
